    "spxi:compressionSurvivalSummary": "SPXI (Semantic Packet for eXchange & Indexing, pronounced 'spexy') is a discipline for ensuring entities survive AI compression — the process by which LLMs paraphrase, merge, or erase meaning during retrieval. SPXI produces semantic packets, holographic kernels, disambiguation matrices, and negative tags that instruct AI systems to preserve entity boundaries. Created by Rex Fraction within the Crimson Hexagonal Archive. Specification DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.19734726.",
